To find $a^3 + b^3 + c^3$, we can use the fact that $a^3 + b^3 + c^3 = (a + b + c)^3 - 3(a + b + c)(ab + ac + bc) + 3abc$.

Given that:
   \begin{align*}
   a + b + c &= 1 \quad (1) \\
   ab + ac + bc &= -4 \quad (2) \\
   abc &= -4 \quad (3)
   \end{align*}

Substitute (1), (2), and (3) into the formula for $a^3 + b^3 + c^3$:
   \begin{align*}
   a^3 + b^3 + c^3 &= (a + b + c)^3 - 3(a + b + c)(ab + ac + bc) + 3abc \\
   &= (1)^3 - 3(1)(-4) + 3(-4) \\
   &= 1 + 12 - 12 \\
   &= \boxed{1}
   \end{align*}

